OL,3,CHow late Bipolar disorder diagnoses
OL,4,Cchanged mine and Angela Rayner's life
OL,6,FIf her mum had received support
OL,7,Fearlier, Rayner thought it may have
OL,8,Ftransformed her life.
OL,10,FThe comment immediately turned my mind
OL,11,Fto my brother - who also suffered with
OL,12,FBipolar disorder but sadly died at the
OL,13,Fage of just 37. Had he been diagnosed
OL,14,Fmuch earlier - would things have been
OL,15,Fdifferent for him too?
OL,17,FMy experience of watching a loved one
OL,18,Fride the rollercoaster highs and lows
OL,19,Fof this illness was not always bad, by
OL,20,Fany means.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G4/21
OL,2,W/*%+.!/*%/"-$ /*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,
