OL,3,CHow late Bipolar disorder diagnoses
OL,4,Cchanged mine and Angela Rayner's life
OL,6,FMy brother was highly intelligent and
OL,7,Fone of the most brilliantly creative
OL,8,Fpeople I'd ever known. He won a place
OL,9,Fat Cambridge University, as well as
OL,10,Fbeing a wonderful musician, talented
OL,11,Fartist and the type of friend from
OL,12,Fwhom love just poured out.
OL,14,FBut his mental illness also brought
OL,15,Fhuge pain and confusion, leaving him
OL,16,Fand us feeling - at times - utterly
OL,17,Fhelpless.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/21
