OL,3,CHow late Bipolar disorder diagnoses
OL,4,Cchanged mine and Angela Rayner's life
OL,6,FThe Royal College of Psychiatrists
OL,7,Fcall that delay "unacceptable". They
OL,8,Fwarn of a "lost decade" in which
OL,9,Fpeople can lose jobs, relationships,
OL,10,Fhomes and even lives.
OL,12,FFor some that is down to suicide - for
OL,13,Fothers - like in our case - it is more
OL,14,Fcomplicated.
OL,16,FNow, the College is calling for that
OL,17,Fdecade-long delay to be urgently cut
OL,18,Fin half.
