OL,3,CHow late Bipolar disorder diagnoses
OL,4,Cchanged mine and Angela Rayner's life
OL,6,FMy brother had the wonderful support
OL,7,Fof medical parents who knew how to get
OL,8,Fhim to the right care, but even in the
OL,9,Fmost acute settings, that Bipolar
OL,10,Fdiagnosis and therefore the most
OL,11,Fappropriate treatment was delayed.
OL,13,FIn the end, he died of a physical,
OL,14,Flung-related disease, but we don't
OL,15,Fbelieve he would have fallen ill if it
OL,16,Fweren't for the risks he took as a
OL,17,Fresult of his Bipolar.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G11/21
