OL,3,CHow late Bipolar disorder diagnoses
OL,4,Cchanged mine and Angela Rayner's life
OL,6,FAs a child, Rayner told me she did not
OL,7,Fhave the words to describe what was
OL,8,Fhappening. "For me, it wasn't a title
OL,9,For condition. It was more, why is my
OL,10,Fmum different? My friends, their mums
OL,11,Fwere able to have their clothes ready
OL,12,Fin the morning for them for school,
OL,13,Fthey would make their breakfast."
OL,15,FShe described asking friends if she
OL,16,Fcould go round for tea, and if their
OL,17,Fparents said no (because it was the
OL,18,Fsecond day in a row) she would sit on
OL,19,Fthe curb and wait. "I always remember
OL,20,Ffeeling hungry as a child," she said.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G12/21
OL,2,W/*%+.!/*%/"-$ /*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,
