OL,3,CHow late Bipolar disorder diagnoses
OL,4,Cchanged mine and Angela Rayner's life
OL,6,FBouts of depression were punctuated
OL,7,Fwith strange highs. "I wanted to be
OL,8,Fthe fastest person to run around the
OL,9,Fwhole world," he said - gesticulating
OL,10,Fin a circle.
OL,12,F"I was starting to come up with plans
OL,13,Ffor how I would run over the water."
OL,15,FThis revved up energy was a sign of
OL,16,Fhypomania, though he did not know it
OL,17,Fat the time. What he did know: was
OL,18,Fthat more and more friends seemed to
OL,19,Fbe drawing away from him.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G17/21
OL,2,W/*%+.!/*%/"-$ /*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,
