OL,3,CHow late Bipolar disorder diagnoses
OL,4,Cchanged mine and Angela Rayner's life
OL,6,FThen came full-blown psychosis. "That
OL,7,Fwas really rough. I was hallucinating,
OL,8,Fseeing things that weren't there, also
OL,9,Fhearing things that weren't there. I
OL,10,Fhad strange, very peculiar delusions."
OL,12,FSam was struggling to hold down work
OL,13,Fby then, so to raise some extra money
OL,14,Fhe volunteered for a research project
OL,15,Fwhich involved Sameer Jauhar - a
OL,16,Fpsychiatrist at Kings College London.
OL,18,FSameer carried out a brain scan on
OL,19,FSam. Pairing that with a detailed
OL,20,Fhistory of his symptoms, he thought he
OL,21,Fknew what might be going on.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G18/21
OL,2,W/*%+.!/*%/"-$ /*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,
