OL,3,CHow late Bipolar disorder diagnoses
OL,4,Cchanged mine and Angela Rayner's life
OL,6,FSoon Sam had a diagnosis for Bipolar
OL,7,Fdisorder four and a half years after
OL,8,Fhis symptoms started - much shorter
OL,9,Fthan the average 9.5.
OL,11,FWhat did that early diagnosis mean for
OL,12,FSam? "I don't think I'd be alive
OL,13,Ftoday," he answered immediately.
OL,15,F"There's many different ways I could
OL,16,Fhave died," he said - arguing that he
OL,17,Ffelt suicidal at times, but also
OL,18,Fbehaved recklessly when psychotic -
OL,19,Fonce being hospitalised after trying
OL,20,Fto down a liter of rum when challenged.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G19/21
OL,2,W/*%+.!/*%/"-$ /*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,
